IC50_Mean_Qualifier: This qualifier is to be used with the next TID, IC50_Mean. If the qualifier is =, the IC50 result equals the value in that column. If the qualifier is >, the IC50 result is greater than that value. If the qualifier is <, the IC50 result is smaller than that value
IC50_Mean: IC50 value determined using a sigmoidal dose response equation
IC50_Qualifier_1: This qualifier is to be used with the next TID, IC50_1. If the qualifier is =, the IC50 result equals the value in that column. If the qualifier is >, the IC50 result is greater than that value. If the qualifier is <, the IC50 result is smaller than that value
IC50_1: IC50 value determined using a sigmoidal dose response equation
Std.Err(IC50)_1: Standard Error of the IC50 value
nH_1: Hill coefficient determined using sigmoidal dose response equation
Excluded_Points_first_point: Flags to indicate which of the first dose-response points were excluded from analysis. (1) means the titration point was excluded and (0) means the point was not excluded.
IC50_Qualifier_2: This qualifier is to be used with the next TID, IC50_2. If the qualifier is =, the IC50 result equals the value in that column. If the qualifier is >, the IC50 result is greater than that value. If the qualifier is <, the IC50 result is smaller than that value
IC50_2: IC50 value determined using a sigmoidal dose response equation
Std.Err(IC50)_2: Standard Error of the IC50 value
nH_2: Hill coefficient determined using sigmoidal dose response equation
Excluded_Points_second_point: Flags to indicate which of the second dose-response points were excluded from analysis. (1) means the titration point was excluded and (0) means the point was not excluded.
